================================================================================
Third-party material
================================================================================

This project is built on the Rust embedded ecosystem for the NXP i.MX RT family
and the Teensy 4. These crates are fetched by Cargo at build time and are NOT
redistributed in this repository; each is distributed under permissive terms
(dual MIT OR Apache-2.0 unless noted). Their copyrights remain with their
respective authors.

  * teensy4-bsp, teensy4-panic, teensy4-pins, teensy4-fcb
        The teensy4-rs project (https://github.com/mciantyre/teensy4-rs).
        Provides the board support package, the i.MX RT boot image (FlexSPI
        Configuration Block / Image Vector Table, via teensy4-fcb), and the
        panic handler.

  * imxrt-rt, imxrt-hal, imxrt-ral, imxrt-iomuxc, imxrt-dma, imxrt-usbd
        The imxrt-rs project (https://github.com/imxrt-rs/imxrt-hal).
        Provides the runtime (boot image generation, memory map, linker script
        t4link.x) and the hardware abstraction / register access layers.

  * rtic, rtic-monotonics, rtic-core, rtic-common, rtic-time
        The Real-Time Interrupt-driven Concurrency framework (https://rtic.rs).
        Provides the async task scheduler and the SysTick monotonic timer used
        by the tasking binary.

  * cortex-m, cortex-m-rt
        The rust-embedded project (https://github.com/rust-embedded/cortex-m).
        Cortex-M core peripheral access and the cycle-delay primitive.

See Cargo.toml and Cargo.lock for the exact crates and resolved versions.

